cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a new approach for unsupervised visual domain adaptation using deep learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the optimization of the model, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. Additionally, the paper uses the Riemannian distance, which is a mathematical concept, indicating that it may belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. The paper also experiments on the Office dataset, which is a common benchmark dataset for domain adaptation, suggesting that it may belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) category. Finally, the paper uses deep learning techniques, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) category.
